                            <h1>Visa related information to foreign attendees of ICBLE 2023</h1>
                            <p>All foreign nationals attending the conference are required to apply for a conference
                                visa. For getting an Indian Visa, the following documents are required. The requirements
                                are:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Original passport – validity not less than 6 months</li>
                                <li>Visa fee</li>
                                <li>Two passport size photographs</li>
                                <li>Supporting documents, wherever necessary</li>
                                <li>An invitation letter from ICBLE 2023 (Invitation letters will be issued after
                                    registration)</li>

                            </ul>
                            <p>
                                These requirements may vary for some countries from where the candidate intends to
                                depart for India. Hence you are advised to please check the documents required from the
                                Consular section of Indian Embassy in respective countries.
                            </p>
                            <h1>Please follow the instructions below to apply for your Visa to attend ICBLE 2023:</h1>
                            <h2>Type of Visa: Conference Visa</h2>
                            <strong>Period: For the duration of the conference including special events</strong>
                            <p>The Consular Passport and Visa (CPV) Division of the Ministry of External Affairs is
                                responsible for issuance of Indian Visas to the foreign nationals for their visit. This
                                facility is granted through the Indian missions abroad.</p>
                            <strong>Procedure for Obtaining Visa</strong>
                            <p>
                                Visas can be applied for in person or by post at the High Commission of India based in
                                the country from where the candidate intends to depart for India. You may also apply
                                online at: https://indianvisaonline.gov.in/visa/# and click on regular visa application.
                                You will then fill up the required details and once you go to Visa category, there you
                                have multiple options of visa application, wherein you should get Conference Visa
                                option. Please select the Conference Visa.
                            </p>
                            <div class=" img-responsive"> <img src="./images/ss.jpg" alt=""> </div>
                            <p class=" mt-4">
                                Visa fees are non-refundable and subject to change without notice. The High Commission
                                reserves the right on granting and deciding type/ duration of visa irrespective of the
                                fees tendered at the time of making application. Granting of Visa does not confer the
                                right of entry to India and is subject to the discretion of the Immigration Authorities.
                            </p>
